1. Passive listening devices for example: iPhone. should be able to capture the noise generated by the surrounding environment. This information should use for study the environment in which one habitated.
The data can be used in the following ways:
1. Recommend how to improve the quality of living, by identified the source in which the sound produces. i.e. In home, at work. where it produces the high discrble in relative to the heart rate one exhibits, when change in environment.
2. The zone of the geographical noise level. This data can be used to provide migration or improvement of existing zone. For example: the change when introduce new airport vs without the airport.


1. The air quality in which one exists. (Co2 (Nest Smoke Detector), Nokia (Home Secure)) for example. should be installed to capture indoor and outdoor airquality. those devices should be subsidized for environment control. 
